  "repo_truth": "Fresh read-only review of the exact complete HCM-2.2 seven-times-remediated planning subject. Review 7 required the live HCM-2.1 commit, resolving content-addressed bootstrap refs, distinct add-enrollment identity, one representable ES256/none protocol branch, exact registry-admin engine/JSON DTOs, and executable raw-intent commit-marker bytes. The subject remains planning-only; inherit no clean conclusion.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay the sorted complete manifest and aggregate fingerprint before review.",
    "Review every subject byte: 00, 04, 06, seven immutable prior dispatches, SPEC, all exact contract/schema/vector/JCS/transcript/API fixtures, plan, unchecked todo, planning proof, and seven remediation records.",
    "Read unchanged 01, 02, 03, 05, 07, 08, HCM-0.6 decision, selected HCM-2.1 record/packet/proof, exact live definition assets, and engine/compiler/flow/CLI/skill/template/test sources only as needed.",
    "Run bounded read-only exact schema/JCS/fingerprint/profile/intake, decoded CTAP2 CBOR/P-256/transcript, content-addressed ref/ID/byte, registry-admin DTO, marker/recovery, Markdown/link, Git, handoff, security, bridge, and classification checks.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence through the built-in channel."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No edits, staging, commits, new dispatches, global handoffs, ledger writes, or user task hops.",
    "No Rust, Cargo, production definitions, runtime fixtures/tests/product/generated-skill/pipeline, HCM-2.3+, Phase-3, SDK, Tauri, Substrate, contract, dock, or publication implementation.",
    "Do not invent alternate schema/intake bytes, fingerprint/ref behavior, approval/identity/registry trust, transaction visibility, lifecycle, renderer, migration, compatibility mode, bridge, or sibling-family scope.",
    "Do not treat prior findings/remediation, passing reproduction, or contingent planning status as proof that the 35-entry subject is clean."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke required skills in order, remain read-only, replay the exact complete manifest/aggregate, and return BLOCKED if any byte differs.",
    "Review findings first in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order with exact file/line, violated authority, failure, smallest remediation, and missing or invalidated proof.",
    "Reproduce all ten exact schema documents/entries, eleven definition JCS vectors, thirteen complete runtime records including six published-schema validations, six approver-admin API vectors, seven registration/assertion transcripts, strict CBOR/P-256 decoding, content-addressed bootstrap ref/ID/fingerprint/byte equality, distinct add-enrollment equality, complete 16-entry profile schema sources, dependency graph, fingerprints, old-byte preservation, and independent encoders/decoders.",
    "Verify the full literal sixteen-row intake, schema/retained-field validation value, every leaf source, value-versus-quality-waiver rule, all-mode equivalence, and candidate basis.",
    "Verify registration-bound bootstrap transition; assertion-bound later transitions; the exact ES256/fmt-none branch; protocol-valid bootstrap and distinct add make-credential responses; exact four engine operation signatures, CLI mappings, closed JSON request/success/refusal DTOs; non-empty admin/quorum/current-pair coverage; and native refusal.",
    "Verify exact 72-byte raw-intent-hash markers, total registry and lifecycle recovery-before-intent steps/tables, ownership-free promotion recovery, every partial staged/final/marker state, advanced-head violation, lock order, authority visibility, and crash/concurrent-reader proof.",
    "Verify canonical/Markdown byte grammars/fixtures, C03/C04, product cutover, bridges, proof wall, deletion gates, CRITICAL impact warning, planning-only status, primary commit, and separate parent closeout.",
    "Return CLEAN only if no valid Critical or Required finding remains; otherwise CHANGES_REQUIRED or BLOCKED. Make no edits."
  ],
